messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /printshops/{id}/reviews

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so the endpoint paths are exactly the values in the method-level @RequestMapping annotations.
- getPrintShopReviews is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.GET) → GET is supported for /printshops/{id}/reviews.
- addPrintShopReview is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.POST) → POST is also supported for the same path.
- PUT and DELETE methods exist in this controller but are mapped to the different path /printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId} (they include the additional {reviewId} path parameter), so they do not apply to /printshops/{id}/reviews.
- There are no explicit @RequestMapping entries for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE or PATCH on the path /printshops/{id}/reviews in the source code, so those methods are not considered acceptable based on the code alone.
